	   <tr><td colspan=2>After playing EQ for the short time of 2 months (which equals 9 days, 9 hours of played game time), a few things have become abundantly clear. One, there are many helpful, supportive, fun players out there who make EQ a more enjoyable game for everyone and we should all aspire to be like them. Two, there are many players who love to criticize, mock and impede newer players and we should avoid them. Next, I keep reading posts from players who levelled to 50 in a week, soloed Nagafen/Cazic Thule/Mayong Mistmoor with their level 38 mage or had a full suit of enchanted elven chain at level 3 because of awesome roleplaying skills that only they possess. These things are completely untrue 99% of the time, so disbelieve them and realize that whatever progress your making is probably the same progress as every other mage in all of Norrath. Finally, there is no best class/race/pet/item/armor/etc. There is merely good playing and bad playing and variations therein. <br><br>Just my 2cp, but I say keep conjuring and evoking and all good things will come in time.<br>&nbsp;<br>Aaneldarie Tura'Seorsa<br>29th Season Magician  Vazaelle</td></tr>
