	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dim pockets are great for a day of hunting. There will be many times when they will come in handy. If your using regular backpacks before long you will be overweight and have to leave loot on the ground. This is when the dim pockets start comming in handy. I always have 2 real backpacks for the real good items. But everthing else goes into the pockets. I'm never overweight. And if I ld I only loose what I would have had to leave on the ground. <br><br>At higher lvl's you will want to have 1 of the real backpacks for gems both pet and armor. At 52nd lvl I still use them a lot. So a very good spell.<br><br>Keep a couple real backpacks in the bank for if your going to hunt dungeons where good loot drops more often. But normally 2 real and the rest dim pockets is a good idea.<br><br>Oh one last thing. When you get to the lvl of hunting kedge keep they are invaluable. You can summon a pack fill it with waterstones and hand them to by the backpack to the members of the raid.<br><br>Makes it a lot easer.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
