	   <tr><td colspan=2>Both of these spells cost around 4pp5gp, just like most of your other level 8 spells.<br><br>You'll be KOS in Neriak if you chose to follow a "good" deity. Some human mages choose to follow evil deities, and while they aren't just welcomed with open arms into Neriak, they usually aren't killed on sight either.<br><br>The Staff of Tracing is far from a "horrible" weapon for a level 8 character. It has the same stats as a warped great staff (and better stats than a worn great staff) with the benefits of a lighter weight and the ability to hit magic creatures. At level 8, the staff will indeed help your pet hit for higher damage, and it is necessary at these levels to give your pet a magic weapon in order to hit creatures like willowisps and elementals.<br><br>The summoned bag also has many uses. I like to keep my summoned food, water, and bandages in a summoned bag...it doesn't matter if I go linkdead, because I'm not losing anything of value. It does keep my carry weight down and frees up other inventory space for loot items.<br><br>I more than paid for my Dimensional Pocket spell hunting rock dervishes in Lavastorm from levels 12-16. The blocks of ore they drop are very heavy, so many players leave them to decay on the corpse; I put them in an extra dimensional pocket and sold them to the gypsies for 4gp apiece. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
