	   <tr><td colspan=2>Until you get a little better at grouping I would listen to the ones who are more exp. at it.  Soon you will know what to do.  Most groups will decide what each is to do before they start battling, especially if you have more than one bard, healers, etc.<br><br>The key to grouping is communication.  As you get higher in levels each group needs to become more and more organized or the MOB will wipe the floor with you.  A lot of people will find a group they trust and pretty much stick with that group.  There are bad groups and if you get into one you usually will find this out quickly.  No communication or organization.<br><br>So know that I am done rambling, yes listen to the leader.  We had one who didn't and got left behind in an emergency evac.  Make sure everyone knows there role in the group.  No need for two bards to be playing the same healing song, or for a cleric and a druid casting heal on the same person.  I guess that last example also covers communication.  Take care and good hunting.<br>&nbsp;<br>Azamar<br></td></tr>
