<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98716967058312></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98716967058312><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98716967058312>RE: Where To hunt at 29</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98716967058312#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>385 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 13th 9:47 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At level 29 there is very good soloing in the Ocean of Tears. On sister island (the first stop going from freeport to butcherblock) you will find two dwarfs that are near a rock on opposite side of the island from the docks. One of them is level 24 and the the other is level 25. You can get to level 34 here by soloing them. <br><br>There is also another dwarf on the island who is either level 24 or 25(I forget). He is standing next to a dwarven marchant on the backside side of the island.<br><br>Also on the island are higher level sisters of erollisi. The ones you will want to hunt are level 25. Hunting these two girls will get you to level 35. One of them stands on the docks. The other stands next to a tree near the docks. I found it was best to to stand at the end of the docks to fight them. While standing here, you can kill both of them without aggroing the other.<br><br>Both the dwarfs and the sisters move faster than normal, so be careful. You might want to use an earth pet is you are having problems with the aggro. If your not having problems with the aggro, then this a great spot to use the fire pet. The air and water pets will still work if you don't want to use a fire pet.<br><br>Former Addict of Everquest.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
