	   <tr><td colspan=2>Also another issue is that if your pet does 50% or more of the damage your xp is cut in half.  I only time i use pet heals is while farming and that is only because i am in a hurry and nuking is too expensive to waist on low lvl mobs.  The stratagy I have chosen at mid lvls is to do DDs till the mob gets to almost half life then allow my pet to take the mob till it is almost dead and throw in a small nuke to finish the job for good messure. This allows for max xp and time to med up while pet is taking on mob. Also evens out yours and your pets down time.  At lvl 51+, if you chose to solo, it is best to nuke till mob is dead.  Mobs at this lvl hit hard and though a magician pet at this lvl can take a beating it is best not to risk it dying because once it is dead you are dead and at that LvL xp is worked hard for and takes a long time to replenish.<br><br>Rrah - 51 elementalist<br>(A pet is a good asset to a mage untill lvl 49, then the mage is a good asset to his pet)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
